  "texts": [
    "In light of these ambiguities, our tool gives developers the ability to exclude OpenAI-generated datasets.",
    "Despite these pervasive legal uncertainties, practitioners can still make some informed decisions to minimize risk if they have reliable data provenance information.",
    "With access to this information, practitioners can decide to err on the side of caution and to use only data licenced for commercial use, contact dataset creators of restrictively licenced data to negotiate a usage agreement or decide that their specific context and risk tolerance allows them to use datasets licenced for non-commercial use.",
    "Through our audit and tooling, we seek to provide the information needed to make informed decisions in an otherwise ambiguous landscape.",
    "Model providers may also consider strategies for partially mitigating uncertainties for downstream users, for example, by indemnifying users, as done by Google Cloud 62."
